HEADWORD: Muskogees
<hw>Mus*ko"gees</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Muskogee</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>
<def>A powerful tribe of North American Indians that formerly occupied
the region of Georgia, Florida, and Alabama. They constituted a large
part of the Creek confederacy.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Muscogees</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

